  content: '\n' +
    '<h2>Overview</h2>\n' +
    '<p>Below, you can read instructions for importing and publishing <a href="https://twinery.org/">Twine</a> stories. Click the link above to view the instructions as a <a href="https://docs.google.com/document/d/1sSsjAZX15zcK-pxHgJNkIgFdkziIEOEmamyKQ0NxOUg/edit">printable Google Doc</a>.</p>\n' +
    '<h3>Directions for Publishing a Twine Story</h3>\n' +
    '<ol>\n' +
    '  <li>Click Build and choose ‘Publish to File’. A HTML file will be automatically downloaded to your device.</li>\n' +
    '  <li>Open your Google Drive on your device. Click ‘New’ then ‘File upload’.</li>\n' +
    '  <li>Locate the new HTML file on your device (probably in Downloads) and select. Then choose ‘Upload/Open’.</li>\n' +
    '  <li>Right click on the file in drive and choose ‘+ share’. Make sure the link at the bottom is set to ‘Anyone with a link can view’.\n' +
    '    <ul>\n' +
    '      <li>If sharing in Google Drive, enter your teacher’s last name at the top and then “Send”</li>\n' +
    '      <li>If sharing via email, click “Copy link” at the bottom left. Then paste the link in an email. This will allow others to import your file and read your story.</li>\n' +
    '    </ul>\n' +
    '  </li>\n' +
    '</ol>\n' +
    '<h3>Directions for Importing a Twine Story</h3>\n' +
    '<ol>\n' +
    '  <li>Click on the Google Drive file and in the top right hand side, click the Download icon (if not visible, click the three dots and then Download).</li>\n' +
    '  <li>Go to Twinery.org and click Use in your Browser. Click ‘Library’ and ‘Import’.</li>\n' +
    '  <li>Locate the new HTML file on your device (probably in Downloads) and select. Then choose ‘Open’. In Twine, select the small box and then ‘Import Selected Files.’</li>\n' +
    '  <li>Your copy of the file will now be in your Library for you to edit.</li>\n' +
    '</ol>\n' +
    '<p>::nsf[2010256]</p>\n',
